{"questionId":"27769","questionHtml":"<p>By considering&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>n</mi></msup></math>&nbsp;as a geometric series, for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>≠</mo><mn>1</mn></math>,&nbsp;show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>uses&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>S</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mi>r</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p>clear indication there are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> terms&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mrow><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &